41
It is principally in consequence of
improvements made in our Instruments
of experiment that the Sciences
have been so much extended
& that they have been made
the common property having
inclinations for studying them
& patience for pursuing them. –
Doctrinal speculations at
present cease to be formidable
in their influence; & variety
of opinion & [deletion]of the[/deletion] freedom
of thought can only produce
benefits in a department
of Knowledge where the
appeal is to Nature &
with [insertion]lofty[/insertion] pride [unclear][deletion]xxxx[/deletion][/unclear] meet his [deletion]high[/deletion] disdain

